  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p>Compound <b>A</b>, C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O, is one of the basic building blocks of nature. All steroids and many other naturally occurring compounds are built from compound <b>A</b>. Spectroscopic analysis of <b>A</b> yields the following information:</p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:none\">\n<li>IR: 3400 cm<sup>–1</sup>; 1640 cm<sup>–1</sup></li>\n<li><sup>1</sup>H NMR: 1.63 <i>δ</i> (3 H, singlet); 1.70 <i>δ</i> (3 H, singlet); 3.83 <i>δ</i> (1 H, broad singlet); 4.15 <i>δ</i> (2 H, doublet, <i>J</i> = 7 Hz); 5.70 <i>δ</i> (1 H, triplet, <i>J</i> = 7 Hz)</li>\n</ul>",
